> To clarify the content of the files above:
> 
> ```
> // FileIO.dfy
> replaceable module DafnyStdLibs.FileIO {
>   method OpenFile(n: string) returns (s: string)
> }
> ```
> 
> ```
> // FileIOForJava.dfy
> module DafnyStdLibs.JavaFileIO replaces DafnyStdLibs.FileIO {
>   method OpenFile(n: string) returns (s: string) {
>     // Likely other validation/conversion to do here.
>     // This is close to the existing implementation that does all of that in Java code instead.
>     s := INTERNAL_openFileExtern(n);
>   }
> 
>   method {:extern} INTERNAL_openFileExtern(n: string) returns (s: string)
> }
> ```
> 
> ```java
> // FileIO.java
> package DafnyStdLibs.JavaFileIO;
> 
> public class DafnyStdLibs.JavaFileIO {
>   public static Dafny.Sequence<Character> INTERNAL_openFileExtern(Dafny.Sequence<Character> n) {
>     // ...actually read the file
>   }
> }
> ```
> 
> So Dafny user code depending on the standard library only sees what's in `FileIO.dfy`, but when compiled to Java ends up depending on the contents of all three, which are in `DafnyRuntime.jar`.

Thanks for explaining the details.

Right now you intend to compile FileIOForJava.dfy into java and include it in the runtime library so that it's never compiled/included twice, correct?
The problem I have with this approach is that it's no longer possible to replace the standard library shipped with a version of Dafny with another standard library (i.e. an updated version)

The problem of duplication essentially comes from if someones compiles two applications using Dafny into Java, and these two applications will thus define the same binaries. Then that user can no longer create an application that uses the previous two applications.
However, if that user delays the compilation and only perform compilation after including all the Dafny libraries and target-specific backend file, then no duplication exists.
This is a strong hint for me that a better way to ship the standard library for Dafny is to ship the files, stored in plain in Dafny.exe and regurgitated on demand, and not include them or precompile them in the Dafny Runtime.

